Your responsibilities
• Develop machine learning models (and XAI components to explain those models) in areas such as anomaly detection in IFRS17 calculations, insurance pricing and others
• Develop PoCs of new solutions as well as deploy machine learning models in production
• Actively contribute to strengthening of the data science/machine learning offering within the actuarial practice;
• Develop new products/services and participate in their marketing and sales;
• Manage junior colleagues as part of larger projects, provide on-the-job training and coaching;
• Work with clients throughout the whole project cycle: sales, delivery and closure;
• Work with other Deloitte colleagues from Polish as well as international offices.
Our requirements
• At least 4 years of experience in machine... learning, actuarial or statistical modeling areas;
• Practical knowledge of machine learning and data science concepts, frameworks and algorithms and ability to explain such concepts to business stakeholders;
• Practical knowledge of Python or R including common libraries for machine learning and data processing;
• Practical knowledge of SQL;
• Creativity and willingness to develop data science related offering;
• Team player with strong interpersonal and communication skills;
• University degree in Data Science, Actuarial Mathematics, Statistics or related;
• Very good command of the English language.
Optional
• Exposure to data science in either life or non-life insurance;
• Knowledge of cloud based solutions (AWS/Azure/GCP);
• Knowledge of best practices in MLOps / deploying machine learning models in production;
• Knowledge of explainable AI techniques and visualisations;
• Knowledge of SAS (4GL and macroprogramming, SAS EG, SAS VA);
• Knowledge of version control systems (e.g. Git);
• Experience with big data processing tools (e.g. Spark);
• Experience with data visualization tools (e.g. R shiny, Tableau/PowerBI);
• Exposure to actuarial software (Earnix , Prophet);
What we offer
• A unique opportunity to develop the advanced analytics offering for insurance business;
• Participation in innovative projects;
• Continuous career development opportunities;
• Friendly team atmosphere and excellent working conditions;
• Wide range of trainings and knowledge development opportunities;
• Access to the state-of-the-art tools and systems;
• Unlimited personal development opportunities (soft skills, project management trainings, foreign language courses, incl. German etc.);
• Flexible working hours and conditions.
Benefits
